OL,3,C'Christmas miracle' as pub devastated
OL,4,Cby flooding reopens
OL,6,F"What we actually woke up to, was
OL,7,Fabout four feet worth of water just
OL,8,Fcoming up to the back door, so it was
OL,9,Fa bit of a process to get us out."
OL,11,FTony Walsh, area manager for Premium
OL,12,FCounty Pubs, added: "It has been a
OL,13,Fstress for the last three weeks, but
OL,14,Fwe've got a great bunch working for us.
OL,16,F"They've worked their own little
OL,17,FChristmas miracle to get us open and
OL,18,Fready so we don't disappoint our
OL,19,FChristmas Day guests, obviously, so it
OL,20,Fhas been a stretch but we've got there
OL,21,Fand we're happy that we're open."
